  "text": "In this paper we construct motives for smooth (but not necessarily proper) Deligne-Mumford stacks as objects of Voevodsky's triangulated category of motives DM eff (k, Q). In the proper case, we compare these motives with the Chow motives we get using Toen's equivalence of categories M k ≃ M DM k . Without assuming properness, our construction of the motive of a smooth Deligne-Mumford stack F seems to be the first one. However, in [CITATION_1] Thm 0 .1] Gillet and Soulé constructed a motivic invariant attached to F , namely a complex of Chow motives. We hope to recover their invariant by applying Bondarko's weight functor to M (F ). (See [CITATION_2] Prop. 6.3 .1].) We leave this for a future investigation.",
